  "root_text": {
    "sn1.41:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 1.41 ",
    "sn1.41:0.2": "5. Ādittavagga ",
    "sn1.41:0.3": "Ādittasutta ",
    "sn1.41:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "sn1.41:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "sn1.41:1.3": "Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṁ jetavanaṁ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "sn1.41:1.4": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
    "sn1.41:2.1": "“Ādittasmiṁ agārasmiṁ, ",
    "sn1.41:2.2": "yaṁ nīharati bhājanaṁ; ",
    "sn1.41:2.3": "Taṁ tassa hoti atthāya, ",
    "sn1.41:2.4": "no ca yaṁ tattha ḍayhati. ",
    "sn1.41:3.1": "Evaṁ ādittako loko, ",
    "sn1.41:3.2": "jarāya maraṇena ca; ",
    "sn1.41:3.3": "Nīharetheva dānena, ",
    "sn1.41:3.4": "dinnaṁ hoti sunīhataṁ. ",
    "sn1.41:4.1": "Dinnaṁ sukhaphalaṁ hoti, ",
    "sn1.41:4.2": "nādinnaṁ hoti taṁ tathā; ",
    "sn1.41:4.3": "Corā haranti rājāno, ",
    "sn1.41:4.4": "aggi ḍahati nassati. ",
    "sn1.41:5.1": "Atha antena jahati, ",
    "sn1.41:5.2": "Sarīraṁ sapariggahaṁ; ",
    "sn1.41:5.3": "Etadaññāya medhāvī, ",
    "sn1.41:5.4": "Bhuñjetha ca dadetha ca; ",
    "sn1.41:5.5": "Datvā ca bhutvā ca yathānubhāvaṁ, ",
    "sn1.41:5.6": "Anindito saggamupeti ṭhānan”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn1.41:0.1": "Linked Discourses 1.41 ",
    "sn1.41:0.2": "5. On Fire ",
    "sn1.41:0.3": "On Fire ",
    "sn1.41:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "sn1.41:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery. ",
    "sn1.41:1.3": "Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, ",
    "sn1.41:1.4": "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: ",
    "sn1.41:2.1": "“When your house is on fire, ",
    "sn1.41:2.2": "you rescue the pot ",
    "sn1.41:2.3": "that’s useful, ",
    "sn1.41:2.4": "not the one that’s burnt. ",
    "sn1.41:3.1": "And as the world is on fire ",
    "sn1.41:3.2": "with old age and death, ",
    "sn1.41:3.3": "you should rescue by giving, ",
    "sn1.41:3.4": "for what’s given is rescued. ",
    "sn1.41:4.1": "What’s given has happiness as its fruit, ",
    "sn1.41:4.2": "but not what isn’t given. ",
    "sn1.41:4.3": "Bandits take it, or rulers, ",
    "sn1.41:4.4": "it’s consumed by fire, or lost. ",
    "sn1.41:5.1": "Then in the end this corpse is cast off, ",
    "sn1.41:5.2": "along with all your possessions. ",
    "sn1.41:5.3": "Knowing this, a clever person ",
    "sn1.41:5.4": "would enjoy what they have and also give it away. ",
    "sn1.41:5.5": "After giving and using according to their means, ",
    "sn1.41:5.6": "blameless, they go to a heavenly place.” "
  },
